dataIdInfo.idAbs: This data layer represents roads for Waushara County, Wisconsin in 2018. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, "Waushara_Roads_2018.gdb". [StreetMaster, is a linear feature class that contains the high-low, left-right attributes for addresses. This feature class is used for geocoding and is also used to support dispatching. This file contains the official street name and is used for most County Centerline application needs.]
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [The purpose is to support address range management. This feature class may contain actual high and lows as well as theoretical high and lows.]
